  <mainDescription>A Mentor is an experienced practitioner in a specific software development capability who splits his or her time between&#xD;
practicing and mentoring.&amp;nbsp;Mentoring activities are performed within the structure of a Center of Capability.</mainDescription>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Mentors who have been properly trained and have the right set of skills and experience to mentor other teams are&#xD;
    critical for the adoption of capability improvements.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
  <impactOfNotHaving>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Without dedicated mentors process and tools adoption may be significantly delayed, or not happen at all.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></impactOfNotHaving>
  <reasonsForNotNeeding>If process and tool improvements are trivial, not representing a significant change to the way teams perform their work,&#xD;
mentors are not required.</reasonsForNotNeeding>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:WorkProductDescription>
